Refresh Data → Scheduled or manual

2️⃣ Data Modeling

Relationships

One-to-One (1:1)

One-to-Many (1:N)

Many-to-Many (M:M)

Cardinality → defines how tables relate

Cross-filter direction

Single → Default, filters flow in one direction

Both → Filters propagate both ways (be careful with circular references)

Star Schema → Recommended structure:

Fact tables → transactions, metrics

Dimension tables → attributes, categories

3️⃣ DAX Basics (Data Analysis Expressions)

Aggregations

SUM(Column) → Sum of column

AVERAGE(Column) → Average of column

COUNT(Column) → Counts values

COUNTROWS(Table) → Counts rows in table

Filtering

CALCULATE([Measure], FilterExpression)

FILTER(Table, Condition)

Time Intelligence

TOTALYTD([Measure], DateColumn)

SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(DateColumn)

DATEADD(DateColumn, -1, YEAR)

Logical

IF(Condition, Result1, Result2)

SWITCH(Expression, Value1, Result1, Value2, Result2, …)

Text

CONCATENATE(Text1, Text2) or & operator

LEFT, RIGHT, MID, LEN

Example Measure

Total Sales := SUM(Sales[Amount])
Sales LY := CALCULATE([Total Sales], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(Date[Date]))
